gomodel:SYNGO_4029  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: DCV fusion analysis using NPY-pHluorin in single control or RIM cDKO hippocampal neurons without or with the expression of full-length RIM1α (grey), MUNC13-2 WT (purple).\nFigure 4B-E and Figure S7A-D: Overexpression of MUNC13-2 (WT) restores DCV fusion in hippocampal neurons.\n\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada: The current paper demonstrates a complete abrogation of DCV fusion in RIM cDKO mice which is rescued by overexpression of MUNC13-2. The term \"regulation..\" was chosen based on the relatively partial rescue seen in overexpressed MUNC13-2 neurons as compared to the overexpression in RIM1 neurons.. Experimental description: The MUNC13-2(WT) rescue construct was derived as described in Deng et al., 2011. Upon looking into Deng et al, 2011, the GFP-tagged rat ubMunc13-2 lentivirus was cited to be derived from Rosenmund et al., 2002." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4029" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

